    public class DataCard
extends com.vaadin.flow.component.orderedlayout.HorizontalLayout
implements Serializable, AutoCloseable, com.vaadin.flow.i18n.LocaleChangeObserver, TranslatableComponent
    DataCard -- A generalized card layout. 
         +--------+---------------------------------------------+----------+
     |        | <Header>                                    |          |
     +        +---------------------------------------------+          |
     | <Logo> | <Description>                               | <Margin> |
     +        +---------------------------------------------+          |
     |        | Footer>                                    |          |
     +--------+---------------------------------------------+

    You can set the components into the containers:

    • <Logo> - Image
    • <Header> - HorizontalLayout
    • <Description> - HorizontalLayout
    • <Footer> - HorizontalLayout
    • <Margin> - VerticalLayout

    You can use the following methods to manage the containers:

    • add<container name>(Components ...)
    • add<container name>AsFirst(Component)
    • add<container name>AtIndex(int, Component)
    • remove<container name>(Components ...)
    • remove<container name>All()

    For special treatment you can request the containers itself via get<container name>() to get access to the low level layout functions. Or you can repalce the container itself via set<container name>(HorizontalLayout)

    Since:
    0.1.0 2021-03-28
